verbose_text: According to several international guidelines (such as BSH (British Society for Haematology) and CBO (' Centraal Begeleidingsorgaan ') [XREF_BIBR], the screening cell set must answer to certain requirements such as the inclusion of at least one cell with homozygous expression of the Fy a, Fy b (Duffy antigens), Jk a, Jk b (Kidd antigens), S and s antigens (MNSs antigens) and heterozygous expression for the K (Kell) antigen [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
